comments.text:
The same year saw another wave of attacks directed against Christian churches and prayer halls in Karnataka by the Hindu organisation Bajrang Dal. The violence first erupted on 14 September when about 20 churches were vandalised in various districts of Karnataka including Mangalore, Udupi, and Chikkamagaluru among others.

During the same attacks, several symbols of Christianity were under threat in Tamil Nadu. Three churches in Erode and Karur districts were stoned, a statue of Mother Mary in Krishnagiri was stolen and an idol of Jesus in Madurai was vandalised - all in over five days.,.,.
comments.author: @fuuf7092

comments.text: Fast-forward a couple of years, at least 305 incidents of violence against Christians were recorded in the first nine months of 2021, according to a fact-finding report released by the Association for the Protection of Civil Rights, United Against Hate, and United Christian Forum. Some of these have been reported from states such as Karnataka, Madhya Pradesh, and Uttarakhand.,.
comments.author: @fuuf7092

comments.text: Delhi in that year saw a whole of six attacks on Churches and a Christian school - which included alleged arson attacks on churches in Rohini and Dilshad Garden along with acts of vandalism in churches in Jasola and Vikaspuri.

comments.text: The first attack among these was on December 20, 2022, when a man dressed up as Santa Claus was beaten up by a Hindutva mob in a residential colony in the Makarpura area, Vadodara in Gujarat. comments.text: A year later, amidst the festivities of Christmas, a spate of attacks against Christians angered the community. They eventually staged a protest at Delhi’s Jantar Mantar a few weeks ago, saying that, “Our people are being beaten up.”

comments.text: The following month, members of the Bajrang Dal and the RSS allegedly vandalised a newly set up church in Delhi’s Dwarka area. comments.text: On 12 December 2021, members of Hindu right-wing groups allegedly set fire to Christian religious books in Karnataka’s Kolar district.
